title: Khon La Khob Fah
overview: Once her father is hospitalized, Chanike decide to return home from abroad. However on her return, she finds out that her father has a huge debt and is unable to cover his medical expenses. Her college roommate introduces her to a high paying job out in the suburbs. Chinapat is the owner of a rubber tree plantation and decides to hire her as a favour to his loving cousin, however they do not get along as Chinapat has some anger management issues. In order to avoid being engaged to his mom's friend's daughter, Chinapat proposes to Chanika to marry him for a large sum of money. Will they ever learn to get along?
